am's fault that Abimelech took Sarah."}, {"ref": "Even she herself said, 'He is my brother.'", "text": "The words \u201cshe herself\u201d are used for emphasis to bring attention to Sarah.\""}, {"ref": "I have done this in the integrity of my heart and the innocence of my hands", "text": "This means \"I have done this with good intentions and actions\" or \"I have done this with no evil thoughts or actions.\" Heart and hands are a figure of speech for thoughts and actions. (See: [[:en:ta:translate:metonymy]])"}]}, {"id": "20-06", "tn": [{"ref": "God said to him", "text": "\"God said to Abimelech\""}, {"ref": "in the integrity of your heart you did this", "text": "\"you did this with good intentions\" or \"you did this without evil intentions.\""}, {"ref": "to touch her", "text": "\"to touch Sarah\""}, {"ref": "the man's wife", "text": "\"Abraham's wife\""}, {"ref": "you will live", "text": "\"I will let you live\""}, {"ref": "all who are yours", "text": "\"all of your people\""}, {"ref": "", "text": "[[:en:bible:notes:gen:20:04|<<]] | [[:en:bible:notes:gen:20:08|>>]]"}]}, {"id": "20-08", "tn": [{"ref": "He told all these things to them", "text": "\"He told them everything that God had told him\""}, {"ref": "What have you done to us?", "text": "Abimelech used this rhetorical question to accuse Abraham. It can also be translated as \u201cYou have done something bad to us!\u201d or \u201cLook what you have done to us!\u201d  (See: [[en:ta:translate:rhetoricalquestion]])"}, {"ref": "to us", "text": "The word \"us\" here is exclusive and does not include Abraham and Sarah. If your language uses an exclusive form of \"we\" or \"us,\" use it here (See: [[en:ta:translate:exclusive]])"}, {"ref": "How have I sinned against you", "text": "Abimelech used this rhetorical question to remind Abraham that he had not sinned against Abraham. It can also be translated as \"I have not sinned against you.\" (See: [[:en:ta:translate:rhetoricalquestion]])"}, {"ref": "that you have brought