ites\" in [[en:bible:notes:gen:10:15|10:17]]."}, {"ref": "forced himself on her", "text": "\"had sexual relations with her\" (See: [[:en:ta:translate:euphemism]])"}, {"ref": "He was drawn to Dinah", "text": "\"He wanted to be with Dinah\" or \"He was very attracted to her\" (UDB)"}]}, {"id": "34-04", "tn": [{"ref": "Now Jacob ", "text": "Background Information]])"}, {"ref": "Jacob heard that he", "text": "The word \"he\" refers to Shechem."}, {"ref": "he had defiled ", "text": "<b>he had defiled <b>- Jacob heard that Shechem raped Dinah. \"Defiled\" can be translated as \"dishonored\" or \"disgraced.\" (UDB)"}, {"ref": "held his peace", "text": "\"kept silent\""}]}, {"id": "34-06", "tn": [{"ref": "Hamor\u2026went out to Jacob", "text": "\"Hamor\u2026went to meet Jacob\""}, {"ref": "The men were offended", "text": "\"The men were outraged\""}, {"ref": "he had disgraced Israel", "text": "Here the word \"Israel\" refers to every member of Jacob's family. Israel as a people group was disgraced. Alternate translation: \"he had humiliated the family of Israel\" or \"he had brought shame on the people of Israel.\""}, {"ref": "forcing himself on Jacob's daughter", "text": "See how you translated similar phrases in [[:en:bible:notes:gen:34:01|34:2]]"}, {"ref": "for such a thing should not have been done", "text": "Alternate translation: \"for he should not have done such a terrible thing.\" (See: [[:en:ta:translate:active|Active or Passive]])"}]}, {"id": "34-08", "tn": [{"ref": "Hamor spoke with them", "text": "\"Hamor spoke with Jacob and his sons.\""}, {"ref": "is in love with", "text": "Alternate translation: \"loves her and wants to marry her\" (See: [[:en:ta:translate:idiom|Idiom]])"}, {"ref": "give her to him as a wife", "text": "In some cultures, the parents decide whom their children will marry."}, {"ref": "Intermarry with us", "text": "\"Allow marriages among your people and ours\""}, {"ref": "intermarry", "text": "to marry a member of a different racial, social, re